The protection of your personal data and your privacy is a central concern for the operator of this website. As part of the use of this private website, no personal data is generally collected, stored, or passed on to third parties. The website does not use tracking tools, cookies, or analysis services that could collect personal data.

Should you nevertheless transmit personal data (e.g., by contacting us via email), this is done voluntarily and at your own risk. The transmitted data will be used exclusively to process your request and will not be passed on to third parties unless the operator is legally obliged to do so or you have expressly consented. Please note that data transmission over the Internet (e.g., when communicating by email) can have security gaps. Complete protection of data from access by third parties is not possible.

You have the right at any time to information about the data stored about your person, its origin and recipients, as well as the purpose of storage. You can also request the correction, blocking, or deletion of this data, provided that there are no legal storage obligations to the contrary. The operator reserves the right to refuse requests without giving reasons if they are not related to this website.

